TY  - JOUR
T1  - Stockholder Reactions To Departures and Appointments of Key Executives Attributable To Firings
AU  - Worrell, Dan L.
AU  - Davidson, Wallace N.
AU  - Glascock, John L.
Y1  - 1993/04/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256528
DO  - 10.5465/256528
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 387
EP  - 401
VL  - 36
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study investigated investors' reactions to announcements of the firings of key executives made over the 25-year period 1963?1987. We found announcements containing information about permanent replacements to he associated with positive market reactions, whereas other types of firing announcements resulted in no market response. In addition, outsider appointments were perceived as beneficial immediately, while insider appointments elicited a wait-and-see reaction.
AB  - This study investigated investors' reactions to announcements of the firings of key executives made over the 25-year period 1963?1987. We found announcements containing information about permanent replacements to he associated with positive market reactions, whereas other types of firing announcements resulted in no market response. In addition, outsider appointments were perceived as beneficial immediately, while insider appointments elicited a wait-and-see reaction.
